                                            <h4 class="mt-0 header-title mb-4">Welcome to the International and Transboundary Water Affairs Department  Information Management System (IMS)</h4>
                                            <p class="text-muted mb-5" style="color: #343a40 !important">
                                                The Ministry of Water and Environment (MWE), through its International and Transboundary Water Affairs Department coordinates national efforts to manage shared water resources with the overall objective to secure and safeguard Uganda’s interests in the shared water resources and therefore ensure availability of water to meet her ecosystem and national development needs. The strategic areas of focus are through partnership and cooperative management initiatives through Lake Victoria Basin Commission, (LVBC), Nile Basin Initiative (NBI), Nile Equatorial Lakes Subsidiary Action Program (NELSAP), African Ministers’ Council on Water (AMCOW), Inter-governmental Agency for Development (IGAD) Initiatives, Global Water Partnerships (GWP) and World Meteorological Organization (WMO).
                                            </p>

                                            <h4 class="mt-0 header-title mb-4">The key functions of the Department include among others;</h4>

                                            <p class="text-muted mb-5" style="color: #343a40 !important"> Coordinating the development and reviewing of national policies focusing on transboundary water resources that aims to maximize Uganda’s benefits from the transboundary waters ·         Coordinating the reviewing and updating of national strategic plans for development, conservation, and management of transboundary water resources. ·         Facilitating the acquisition and exchange of water resources data and information with other riparian countries ·         Leading national assessments on the potential impacts of proposed developments on transboundary water on riparian states.</p>
                                            <p class="text-muted mb-5" style="color: #343a40 !important"> Coordinating the participation of Uganda in sourcing of funds for and in implementation of cooperative development of transboundary water projects ·         Directing the development, operation and maintenance of decision support tools and information databases on transboundary water systems.</p> <p class="text-muted mb-5" style="color: #343a40 !important">  Taking custody, and safeguarding transboundary water protocols and agreements to which Uganda is a party. ·         Overseeing the implementation, monitoring and evaluating progress of transboundary water resources projects. ·         Stimulating interest, and raise national level awareness on matters of Nile and other Transboundary water systems.</p> 
                                           
